For installation we leverage fixup_bundle: https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/module/BundleUtilities.html
	- This requires unique APP vars for each OS (see src/CMakeLists.txt for details)

To build on OSX: 

    brew install cmake
	brew install gcc --with-fortran
	brew install fftw 

    git clone git@github.com/bollig/pscf.git
    mkdir pscf-build
    cd pscf-build && cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/path/to/install ../pscf
	make -j 4
	make install 

To build on MSI with Intel Compilers: 

	module load cmake
	module load intel mkl
	module load fftw
	
    git clone git@github.com/bollig/pscf.git
    mkdir pscf-build
    cd pscf-build && cmake -DUSE_INTEL=1 -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/path/to/install ../pscf
	make -j 4
	make install 

To build installers (run this on each target platform: OSX, Linux and Windows): 

	make package

To check the RPM for detailed information (Metadata, Dependencies, and File Contents): 

	rpm --info -qpR -qlvp pscf-1.0.0-Linux.rpm 

To check the DEB for semi-detailed information: 

	# This extracts multiple files
	ar -vx pscf-1.0.0-Linux.deb
	# See the files that would be installed
	tar tvfz data.tar.gz 
